                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.48/2055: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-07T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 7, 1942—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 7—11:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>456. My 447, March 6, 8 p.m. Swedish ships referred to in first paragraph are all
                    oil-burning. British Minister has telegraphed substance of our conversation with
                    Mr. Boheman to his Government. We both hope that earliest possible instructions
                    may reach us so that Swedish Government may go ahead.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
